narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I deepened my understanding of linear algebra, developing many intuitions applicable to physics. I also learned many new topics, such as complex analysis and greens functions. The topics were well chosen to give a broad overview of the areas of math relevant to physics, and we can continue to explore those areas most relevant to our particular area more deeply.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I felt that it went over some topics too quickly, and spent more time on linear algebra than necessary. We spent the entire first half of the semester on linear algebra, then skimmed over complex analysis in two weeks.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: This is an extemely useful class, and taught by one of the masters of mathematical physics. I would highly reconmend this to any student looking at a career in physics research. Do be aware that the notes posted online are not complete.
